        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The &amp;quot;Pandit Dindayal Upadhyay Awas Yojana (Developing Caste Welfare) (NT-DNT)&amp;quot; is a welfare scheme by the Social Justice and Empowerment Department of Gujarat. Under this scheme, eligible applicants from the Nomadic Tribe (NT) and Denotified Tribe (DNT) are given up to ₹1,20,000/- for constructing a house. Priority is given to individuals from BPL families.\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n  - **Financial Assistance:** Up to ₹1,20,000/- for house construction.\n",
        "briefDescription": "The \"Pandit Dindayal Upadhyay Awas Yojana (Developing Caste Welfare) (NT-DNT)\" provides financial assistance of up to ₹1,20,000/- to the people belonging to Nomadic Tribes and Denotified Tribes.\n",
